Baadur Aleksandrovich Jobava vs Aleksandar Indjic
Abu Dhabi Masters (2019), Abu Dhabi UAE, rd 4, Aug-04 
Sicilian Defense: Closed. Chameleon Variation (B23) 


1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. Nge2 g6 4. d4 cd4 5. Nd4 Bg7 6. Nb3 Nf6 7. Be2 d6 8. O-O O-O 9. Re1 b6 10. Bg5 Bb7 11. Qd2 Rc8 12. Bh6 Ne5 13. Bg7 Kg7 14. Qd4 Nc6 15. Qe3 e6 16. Rad1 Qe7 17. Qc1 Rfd8 18. Rd3 Ba6 19. Rh3 Be2 20. Re2 h5 21. f4 Ng4 22. Rf3 a6 23. h3 Nf6 24. Qe1 b5 25. Kh1 Rc7 26. Qf2 Re8 27. a3 Rh8 28. Rd3 h4 29. Red2 a5 30. Qe3 a4 31. Nd4 Na5 32. b3 ab3 33. cb3 Rb7 34. Ncb5 e5 35. fe5 de5 36. Nf5 gf5 37. Qg5 Kf8 38. Rd8 Ne8 39. Re8 Qe8 40. Qf6 Rg8 41. Rd8 Rb5 42. Qh6 Rg7 43. Qd6 Kg8 44. Re8 Kh7 45. Qd7


The 26th Abu Dhabi International Chess Festival takes place from 2-10 August 2019 in Abu Dhabi, UAE. The Masters tournament is a 9-round Swiss open restricted to players with a FIDE rating of 2100 and above.

The winner receives $13,000. The time control is 90 minutes for the entire game plus a 30-second increment starting from move one. Official website: adchessfestival.ae
